org.jbei.ice.lib.net

Class RemotePartner

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jbei.ice.lib.net.RemotePartner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IDataModel

    @Entity
public class RemotePartner
extends Object
implements IDataModel
    Stores information about partners that this registry is involved with in web of registries configuration.
    Field Descriptions:
    • NAME: Name of the registry partner for display purposes. If a partner exists with the specified name, the url is used
    • URL: Unique resource locator for the partner. This is used together with the api key to verify access
    • STATUS: RemotePartnerStatus that is used to indicated whether a partner is blocked or approved. All partners are initially approved unless explicitly blocked by the administrator. Partners that are blocked and attempt to request a search will have that request fail silently. Outgoing requests to blocked partners are also not permitted
    • API_KEY: This is a globally unique identifier received from a partner and used for all communications with that partner.
    • AUTHENTICATION_TOKEN: This is an API_KEY generated on this system and send to other partner. That partner then includes the authentication token as the api key for all requests to this server.
    • ADD_TIME: Time partner was added
    • LAST_CONTACT_TIME: Last time contact was made with partner
    • FETCHED: Number of parts that this system has fetched from partner
    • SENT: Number of parts that this system has sent to partner
    Author:
    Hector Plahar
